<?xml-stylesheet type="text/xsl" href="mathml.xsl"?><html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:pref="http://www.w3.org/2002/Math/preference" pref:renderer="mathplayer-dl"><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=UTF-8" /><link rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" href="opengl-man.css" /><title>glGetFragDataIndex - OpenGL 4 Reference Pages</title><meta name="generator" content="DocBook XSL Stylesheets V1.78.1" /></head><body><div class="refentry"><a id="glGetFragDataIndex"></a><div class="titlepage"></div><div class="refnamediv"><h2>Name</h2><p>glGetFragDataIndex — query the bindings of color indices to user-defined varying out variables</p></div><div class="refsynopsisdiv"><h2>C Specification</h2><div class="funcsynopsis"><table border="0" class="funcprototype-table" summary="Function synopsis" style="cellspacing: 0; cellpadding: 0;"><tr><td><code class="funcdef">GLint <strong class="fsfunc">glGetFragDataIndex</strong>(</code></td><td>GLuint <var class="pdparam">program</var>, </td></tr><tr><td> </td><td>const char * <var class="pdparam">name</var><code>)</code>;</td></tr></table><div class="funcprototype-spacer"> </div></div></div><div class="refsect1"><a id="parameters"></a><h2>Parameters</h2><div class="variablelist"><dl class="variablelist"><dt><span class="term"><em class="parameter"><code>program</code></em></span></dt><dd><p>
                    The name of the program containing varying out variable whose binding to query
                </p></dd><dt><span class="term"><em class="parameter"><code>name</code></em></span></dt><dd><p>
                    The name of the user-defined varying out variable whose index to query
                </p></dd></dl></div></div><div class="refsect1"><a id="description"></a><h2>Description</h2><p>
            <code class="function">glGetFragDataIndex</code> returns the index of the fragment color to which the variable <em class="parameter"><code>name</code></em>
            was bound when the program object <em class="parameter"><code>program</code></em> was last linked. If <em class="parameter"><code>name</code></em> is not a varying out
            variable of <em class="parameter"><code>program</code></em>, or if an error occurs, -1 will be returned.
        </p></div><div class="refsect1"><a id="notes"></a><h2>Notes</h2><p>
            <code class="function">glGetFragDataIndex</code> is available only if the GL version is 3.3 or greater.
        </p></div><div class="refsect1"><a id="errors"></a><h2>Errors</h2><p>
            <code class="constant">GL_INVALID_OPERATION</code> is generated if <em class="parameter"><code>program</code></em> is not the name of a program object.
        </p></div><div class="refsect1"><a id="seealso"></a><h2>See Also</h2><p>
